OK this is my current all time favorite place to eat. The udon and side orders are premium grade and always hot and delicious. BUT THE DRAW IS THAT IS VERY INEXPENSIVE. One of the udon bowls is $3.60 a and it will satisfy you. They also have side fried chicken (my favorite), assorted tempura, musubi, etc all at reasonable prices. The downtown location has adequate seating but go before 12 noon so it isn't busy yet because there WILL be a long line. The place empties out quickly though. Parking is "free" if you buy something at Walmart nearby. There's lots of parking there, it's the old downtown Macy's.  The Waikiki Marukame is smaller, has longer lines and parking starts at about $8 unless you go to Ross' nearby and buy something then parking is free or a lot less. The Waikiki location closes at 10pm while the downtown location closes at 7pm, 7 days a week. Dinner time at the downtown location is usually light so no lines and plenty of open tables. Cafeteria style dining but atmosphere is like Tokyo fast food action.

Definitely a lovely little corner spot for those in a bit of a rush in the business district of Honolulu. The prices are very reasonable and the location is accommodating. Don't think you can park nearby though. The nearest everyday parking would probably be at Walmart which you still have to pay for during the week before 5pm unless you validate with a $10 or more store receipt.  Either way, the food is definitely worth the stop and turned me on to Udon. If you're already a fan of it, you probably have a better opinion than I do but be sure to stop here, check out the simple menu and see for yourself.

One of the best places to eat if you are on a budget.  The food is really good given the price.  There's also a lot of items to choose from ala carte.  There's also a take out line that you can use to get your food faster.
